snippet.textDisplay: I am at work, listening to this song, the beautiful notes drifting into my soul. Maybe its the silk voice of Farida Khanum ji, or the subtle music, or the pain and the sadness in the words or the calm in her voice and in her eyes. This song is like a cold white wave for my parched soul. Flooding it with so many colors of emotions, that I am going to burst into a rainbow. Makes  me long for the love I never had, and makes me sink in the love that I have.  The strains of her timeless voice tells me of a place beyond everything and all. I can never thank her enough for this magical song. God bless you with bountiful health and all the happiness always.
